# HotelAI Coding Standards

Read `docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md` for full details.

## TypeScript

- `strict: true` always; no `any`, no TS `enum` (use string unions)
- Nullable DB columns: `string | null`
- `import type` for type-only imports
- Entity types in `types/`, one file per domain

## Imports (order)

1. React/Next → 2. third-party → 3. `@/lib` → 4. `@/types` → 5. `@/components/ui` → 6. relative

Use `@/` alias, never deep `../../../` paths.

## Exports

- Named exports for components and functions
- Default export only for `app/**/page.tsx`
- Feature barrels via `index.ts`

## Server vs Client

| Server Component | Client Component (`"use client"`) |
|------------------|---------------------------------|
| Route pages, data fetch | useState, useEffect, events |
| `*.service.ts` calls | Forms, tables with actions |
| No hooks or handlers | Realtime, toasts, confirm() |

## Error Handling

```typescript
// Mutations: throw
if (error) throw error;

// Client: catch + toast
try { await action(); toast.success("..."); router.refresh(); }
catch (e) { console.error(e); toast.error("..."); }
```

- Never empty catch blocks
- User messages in Russian
- `confirm()` before delete; no `alert()` in new code

## Forms

- `useTransition` + Server Action on submit
- `disabled={pending}` on submit button
- Optional entity prop for edit mode; `onSuccess` closes dialog

## Git / Env

- Never commit `.env`, secrets, or zip artifacts
- Env: `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL`, `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`
